                h1(style="margin-left:400px; font-family:libraryFont; font-weight:bold") Cold Flu 
                h2(style="margin-left:10px; font-family:libraryFont") General Treatment 
                    h4(style="margin-left:10px") Rest and avoid exercise, drink lots of water, avoid caffiene and maintain a well-balanced diet! 

                h2(style="margin-left:10px; font-family:libraryFont") Specific Treatment
                    h4(style="margin-left:10px; margin-right:5px") If you have a fever, drink fluids containing electrolytes (ex. gatorade powder mix). If it is severe (over 102 fahrenheit), take Acetaminophen or Ibuprofen. If you have a severe and dry cough that is affecting your work and sleep, take Dextromethorphan. If you have a sore throat, gargle some salt water and drink tea if available. If you have a runny nose, take 60mg of Oral decongestants; it will suppress appetite, irritability, and insomnia. Take a hot shower as well as allergy medicaton; this will make you drowsy, do not take it if planning on operating machinery. If this does not work, take 1-2 sprays or 2-3 drops of Topical decongestant per nostril for 3 days. Finally, if you have a wet cough, take an expectorant such as guaifenesin.  

                h2(style="margin-left:10px; font-family:libraryFont") Possible Issues if Left Untreated
                    h4(style="margin-left:10px") If you have a fever of over 100 fahrenheit and severe dry coughing, it could develop into pneumonia. An untreated sore throat with no runny nose could evolve into Bronchitis. If you have a simple cold or flu it could get worse and cause an ear infection.

                h2(style="margin-left:10px; font-family:libraryFont") Preventing Further Issues
                    h4(style="margin-left:10px") Wash your hands often, maintain a consistent exercise routine, sleep 7-8 hours a day, and get a flu shot if there is a licensed astronaut on board!

